{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-500].
  {panel}

Instead of having to create filters to import in portfolio. The ability to create a search on the import screen using JQL to then import would be a time saver.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1700].
  {panel}

With Classic Plans, it is possible to filter the Scope of a plan by Stages, but this functionality no longer exists in Live Plans. This feature was used by many teams, and they would like that functionality restored.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1238].
  {panel}

It appears that after initial import of issues (Stories/Epics) into a given Release in Portfolio, if the source issue is changed in JIRA (e.g. fixversion is updated) this change does not get reflected back up in Portfolio.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1613].
  {panel}

Shared teams are only useful if your team is only working on one portfolio plan at a time.

If you are paralleling work on multiple plans, shared teams don't work because the plans don't take in to account that the team member won't have their full availability for the plan, only a portion of it. This means scheduling using shared teams is very unrealistic. 

It would be best if it were possible to define how many hours per week a member of a shared team can actually dedicate to each plan.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1391].
  {panel}

The releases report will be much more useful if sorting options are available where one can choose to show the cards in release date order.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-534].
  {panel}

In Portfolio we can see the Originally Planned and Estimate (time Remaining) against Epics and Stories. It would be nice to add a column to show the actual time taken (Hours in Total). Today, if I click on the progress bar the card that comes up show 'Hours in Total' but I'd like to see this for all items in the plan without having to click on the progress bar.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1480].
  {panel}

In other areas of JIRA (eg. project version pages), progress bars are shown as 3 colors: grey (no progress), yellow (work in progress) and green (complete).

Could we please see the same progress bars in Portfolio so that our rollups at Epic / Initiative levels demonstrate said progress?

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1275].
  {panel}

In the Epic or Initiative view, I'd like to be able to filter by Initiative so that I can only see information relating to a specific Initiative on the screen.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1725].
  {panel}

The Team field in JIRA that corresponds to teams in Portfolio needs to be a multi-select field.  Initiatives frequently are assigned to multiple teams so the field in JIRA needs to support this.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1749].
  {panel}

As a product manager I would like to link to my working plan with persisted views so the recipient can collaborate on the same view

When a team member needs to update a specific set of data in my plan I want to be able to filter down to that specific set of data and then send the persisted state of my plan to them.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1762].
  {panel}

My team does not use Jira's time tracking, we find it an arduous and cumbersome system for tracking time. Instead, we use subtasks to breakdown our stories into technical steps, each roughly a day's worth of work.

Portfolio would become much more useful to us if it could estimate progress based on completed subtasks instead of relying exclusively on time tracking. If this could be configured per project (time tracking or subtasks), it would give us extra flexibility.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1658].
  {panel}

It would be nice when committing an issue in Portfolio, if the assignee only saw their issues. 

This would avoid users accidentally committing other issues

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1735].
  {panel}

To provide additional context to issues in the scope table

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1477].
  {panel}

Please implement import/export functionality in Portfolio 2.0. It used to work in the older ("classic") version.

The format doesn't matter all that much. It can be XML, JSON, CSV, anything - as long as it works.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1395].
  {panel}

When a sprint is closed in JIRA Agile, the progress against the epic in JIRA Portfolio disappears and the story is no longer visible.

As stories that are in closed sprints are still part of the epic their completion should be taken into account for the epic's progress bar and the stories should remain visible in Portfolio.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1246].
  {panel}

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1202].
  {panel}

If in the option "Stage/sprint constraint" in Plan/Configure - Scheduling - Scheduling Options is set to "Off", the teams in Kanban mode are not fully scheduled based on their capacity.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1629].
  {panel}

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1321].
  {panel}

When mixing issue dependencies and releases with dependent start dates some issues might not be scheduled without a proper warning or error message if there exist cyclic dependencies.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1488].
  {panel}

The default value for the _Completion date_ filter is "Completed since beginning of current sprint", even when the plan contains no sprints (e.g. has only Kanban teams). This leads to counterintuitive behaviour, as people may not realise why completed issues are not being shown.

Either the _Completion date_ filter should default to another value (e.g. "This month"), or the UI should otherwise make it clear why completed issues are not showing.
